title.narrative: By 2020 School Councils and communities have improved accountability to prevent drop_out and absenteeism with special focus on adolescent girls, children with disabilities and childern affected by conflict/disaster

description.narrative: In 2019, the major progress was increased accountability of MINEDH, through continuous training school councils, which created an enabling environment for prevention of early marriage/pregnancy and monitoring drop-out, absenteeism of managers, teachers and students. This was achieved in 2019 through a tripartite partnership between UNICEF, MINEDH and a network of Civil Society Organization (CSOs) resulting in an effective implementation of a new referral and reporting mechanism for prevention of Violence Against Children (VAC) in schools. Lessons learned are the importance to document best practices for advocacy propose with MINEDH and donors and use the evidences to define sustainability strategies. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2020
